fields.Title: JAM / COALITION WARSHIP ARCHER -- SOONA VERSION
fields.Description: CUTSCENE where you attempt to contact Coalition Warship Archer with SOONA. PART OF THE MORALIST DREAM QUEST

fields.Title: You: ""Roy said this transceiver came wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Roy said this transceiver came with some kind of *signal purifier*. Maybe we should turn that on?"

fields.Title: You: ""Yes.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Try again, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Try again, officer."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Then he turns to you. He gives you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then he turns to you. He gives you a half smile along with an almost imperceptible nod of encouragement.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einziges Kind. Er kann doch auch nächstes Jahr zur Akademie gehen."

fields.Title: You: ""What are you talking about, Kim? I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you talking about, Kim? It's perfectly nice out."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""I can't say with certainty, but it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't say with certainty, but it *sounds* very much like entroponetic crosstalk. It happens sometimes when sending transmissions across long stretches of pale."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It sounds very much like entropone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It sounds very much like entroponetic crosstalk. It happens sometimes when sending transmissions across long stretches of pale..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""We must consider several variables..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We must consider several variables: local entroponetic conditions, the sophistication of our transceiver, the quality of our connections, and the physics of our antenna itself."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Damn, I was afraid of that. And I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, I was afraid of that. And I didn't bring any solvents with me. How foolish..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "Through the scrim, you can just mak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Through the scrim, you can just make out the shadow of Coalition Warship Archer a few kilometres to the east.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""That is because you broke it. Thin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That is because you broke it. Things stop working when you break them. Or did you not know that?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Damn it! I'm going to push the pow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn it! I'm going to push the power supply. I doubt it will last more than a few minutes, so you'd better make them count."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: "A loud sigh comes through the headp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A loud sigh comes through the headphones. "Be advised, officer. The signal is liable to fail any moment now..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte... Er ist unser ei..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte... Er ist unser einziges Kind..."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Soona, the Programmer: ""If you'll please carry that amplif..."]
You: ""Maybe we should try again later?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe we should try again later?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "She's right. The responsibility is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's right. The responsibility is yours and yours alone. There's no turning back now.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: "She sighs. "I'm afraid we're out of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She sighs. "I'm afraid we're out of alternatives. You're just going to have to *go for it*."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Come on! Kings and sabres are so *p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Come on! Kings and sabres are so *played out*. There's a *better* way...

fields.Title: You: ""I can't understand a word of this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't understand a word of this gibberish."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""I believe you mean, what *was* he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I believe you mean, what *was* he talking about."

fields.Title: You: ""What is he talking about?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is he talking about?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Is this really the time, detective?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is this really the time, detective?"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "A few of the idle lorry drivers and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A few of the idle lorry drivers and strike breakers gesture at you with their cigarettes, more out of curiosity than anything else. From the window of one of the adjacent apartment buildings, an older woman leans out, her heavy breasts sagging...

fields.Title: You: ""It's not *my* fault the statue bro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not *my* fault the statue broke."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Horseback Antenna: "The lieutenant's final words are ne..."]
You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Firewalker. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate1: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Tequila Sunset. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate2: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Detective Costeau. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate3: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Lieutenant Du Bois. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "You can't make out a word of this g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can't make out a word of this gibberish.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Something about her son going to Vr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something about her son going to Vredefort on an aerostatic... to see some psychologists? Or maybe it's the psychologists saying it's normal... to have feelings for strangers? Foreign languages were never your strong suit.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Ah! Very good thinking. I'll engag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah! Very good thinking. I'll engage it now..."

fields.Title: You: ""Archer! This is Firewalker. Can yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Archer! This is Firewalker. Can you hear me?"
fields.Alternate1: "Archer! This is Tequila Sunset. Can you hear me?"
fields.Alternate2: "Archer! This is Detective Costeau. Can you hear me?"
fields.Alternate3: "Archer! This is Lieutenant Du Bois. Can you hear me?"

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "Chalk powder. Absorbs moisture and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Chalk powder. Absorbs moisture and keeps your grip firm.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "You don't exactly cut a lithesome f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You don't exactly cut a lithesome figure, but after several moments of scrambling you manage to hoist yourself atop the monument.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "... and before you know it, you're..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ... and before you know it, you're safely perched atop the monument.

fields.Title: You: ""Got it. Are we ready?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Got it. Are we ready?"

fields.Title: Shivers: "A soft rustling. The snow seems to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A soft rustling. The snow seems to have gotten between your ears somehow...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""We don't have time for indecision...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We don't have time for indecision. Just say whatever first comes to mind."

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Perhaps you're simply imagining it,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Perhaps you're simply imagining it, but it seems as though you're learning to pull apart the fibres of this auditory felt. You focus on one strand in particular, one that sounds very nearly human...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Not ghosts, officer. Crosstalk. Yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not ghosts, officer. Crosstalk. You have to keep trying until we get a signal through."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's been a long winter... Long an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's been a long winter... Long and cold."

fields.Title: You: ""What can we do?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What can we do?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""You need to climb up there and loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You need to climb up there and look at them for yourself." She stares at you as though it were obvious. Her hand gestures to the colourful cables dangling from the horse's forehooves.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""I sincerely doubt that's the case,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I sincerely doubt that's the case, but there's nothing I can do about it from down here. I should've cleaned them beforehand. How foolish..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "Once the oils have been dissolved,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Once the oils have been dissolved, you wipe off the connections with your sleeve and reattach the cable.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the horse."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the horse.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Keep it together, champ! You've *go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep it together, champ! You've *got* this.

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""This is... Warship Archer. We are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is... Warship Archer. We are acknowledging and accepting you... though we're still getting quite a bit of interference..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Too late. I've begun transmitting...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Too late. I've begun transmitting..."

fields.Title: Shivers: "A soft rustling. Between your ears,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A soft rustling. Between your ears, a winterscape with fast falling snow...

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Lieutenant Harrier du Bois of the RCM. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: You: ""What's going on?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's going on?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Right. I just wish I could remembe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. I just wish I could remember what I was talking about..."

fields.Title: You: ""How am I supposed to inspect the c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How am I supposed to inspect the connections?"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "A clear sky. The kind of day where..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A clear sky. The kind of day where anything might happen...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You allow the broken hunk of metal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You allow the broken hunk of metal to clatter to the ground. It wasn't clear to you it did anything anyway...
fields.Sequence: Hold(); HideActualHeld()@1; BanishInterface(true)@1; LuaRun(SetAreaState("MONUMENT_HEAD_STATE", "broken")); FocusCamera(MonumentFall2Cam)@2; PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, monument_twist_F)@5; PlayAnimation(Horsehead, monument_twist_F)@5; FocusCamera(MonumentHeadCam)@18; FocusCamera(MonumentFall3Cam)@27; PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, monument_twist_F2)@27->Message(onMarker); BanishInterface(false)@Message(onMarker); Release()@Message(onMarker);

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Don't forget the lats, champ! You'v..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't forget the lats, champ! You've *got* this.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The metal bar is cold and slick wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The metal bar is cold and slick with precipitation. For a moment it feels as though you're about to slip, but you concentrate all your attention on your pectoral muscles and squeeze...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""I didn't see anything. I was focus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't see anything. I was focussed on my work. Have you checked the connections yet, or no?"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Something about this set-up seems d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something about this set-up seems dimly familiar, but you'll be damned if you know what you're supposed to do about it.

fields.Title: You: "Wait, what's this "better way"?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, what's this "better way"?

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Try it now.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Try it now."

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "It's too much! Your ear drums are t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's too much! Your ear drums are throbbing, about to burst!

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Detective Raphaël Ambrosius Costeau of the RCM. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: You: ""What should I say?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What should I say?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "I-i-is there anybody th-th-there?"
fields.Dialogue Text: I-i-is there anybody th-th-there?

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Nervous for who, though, you cannot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nervous for who, though, you cannot say.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It's just like that woman in the el..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's just like that woman in the electronic doorbell... the circuit ghost...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""In the meantime, you must keep try..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In the meantime, you must keep trying."

fields.Title: You: ""Could this be more entroponetic cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Could this be more entroponetic crosstalk?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Yes," the programmer cuts in. "A p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes," the programmer cuts in. "A particularly eerie specimen, but still just a harmless piece of the past returning to surface."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Natürlich halten ihn die Psycholog..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Natürlich halten ihn die Psychologen für vollkommen normal..."

fields.Title: You: ""The whole statue's covered in weir..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The whole statue's covered in weird oils. I don't think it's good for the connections."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "More than that, you're sacrificing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: More than that, you're sacrificing something precious on the altar...

fields.Title: You: ""That piece of junk didn't even wor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That piece of junk didn't even work!"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "... but before you can decide what,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ... but before you can decide what, you find yourself safely perched atop the monument.

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""Is everything alright?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is everything alright?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's been a long winter... Long an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's been a long winter... Long and cold."

fields.Title: You: ""Not yet.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not yet."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Then it will be exactly like every..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then it will be exactly like every other moment of every other day. I ask again: Are you ready?"

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Then he turns to you. His expressio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then he turns to you. His expression seems to say, 'You'd better not leave this mess for me alone'.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I didn't say anything, detective.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't say anything, detective."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Glad that stuff came in handy afte..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Glad that stuff came in handy after all..."

fields.Title: Logic: "Not intentionally. It’s a matter of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not intentionally. It’s a matter of perspective. The king was never meant to be seen from such an angle as you’ve attained.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "You turn to the east, but the visib..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You turn to the east, but the visibility is quite poor. You see no sign of Coalition Warship Archer, though you know it can't be too far away.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "His imperious gaze leads you natura..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His imperious gaze leads you naturally to his outstretched hand, which for some reason strikes you as sadly empty...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""But you didn't, you made things wo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you didn't, you made things worse."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""But it *is*, because *you* broke i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But it *is*, because *you* broke it."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""This is the best we can do. I sugg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is the best we can do. I suggest you get to your business quickly. I doubt I'll be able to maintain even *this* connection very long."

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: "Attempt to narrow the receiving mod..."]
You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Firewalker. Do you acknowledge?"
fields.Alternate1: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Tequila Sunset. Do you acknowledge?"
fields.Alternate2: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Detective Costeau. Do you acknowledge?"
fields.Alternate3: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Lieutenant Du Bois. Do you acknowledge?"

fields.Title: You: ""So what can we do about it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So what can we do about it?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""But someone has been maintaining i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But someone has been maintaining it. The wiring has been repaired..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The cold metal chills your bare han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The cold metal chills your bare hands. Some part of your brain tells you something is missing...

fields.Title: You: ""What would changing the shape of t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What would changing the shape of the antenna do?"

fields.Title: You: "That's a little *too* out there. [P..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's a little *too* out there. [Put the sabre in the king's hand.]

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "To your surprise, the sabre slides..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To your surprise, the sabre slides snugly between the horse's bared teeth.

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer. This is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is RCM Officer Firewalker. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate1: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is RCM Officer Tequila Sunset. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate2: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is Detective Costeau of the RCM. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate3: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is Lieutenant Harrier Du Bois of the RCM. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""We're ready to try, at least. Plea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're ready to try, at least. Please, put on these headphones, there should be two extra sets. I've configured the channels so that only your microphone is set to broadcast, officer. We'll all be able to listen, but anyone we reach will only hear *your* voice."

fields.Title: You: "What does this remind me of?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What does this remind me of?

fields.Title: You: ""It's really coming down, now that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's really coming down, now that you mention it."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Well, do you see anything?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, do you see anything?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""What are you doing?! Oh... cleanin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you doing?! Oh... cleaning the connections? Smart."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Officer, I've held the signal open..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, I've held the signal open as long as I can. Whatever you came here to ask, ask it now."

fields.Title: You: ""Hello... Archer? Do you acknowledg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello... Archer? Do you acknowledge?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's cold now...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's cold now..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... Warship Archer. Are you there,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Warship Archer. Are you there, Firewalker? Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate1: "... Warship Archer. Are you there, Tequila Sunset? Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate2: "... Warship Archer. Are you there, Detective Costeau? Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate3: "... Warship Archer. Are you there, Lieutenant Du Bois? Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... Warship Archer. Please identif..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Warship Archer. Please identify."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, you're a natural gymnast, det..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, you're a natural gymnast, detective. Now would you like to do what you got up there to do?"
fields.Alternate1: "You're doing alright, detective. Just keep your focus on the task at hand."

fields.Title: You: "Attach the sabre."
fields.Dialogue Text: Attach the sabre.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""... a long winter... Long and cold..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... a long winter... Long and cold..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's done. I believe we're ready."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's done. I believe we're ready." The lieutenant wipes his brow.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You're all alone out there, wanderi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're all alone out there, wandering a blasted heath, calling out to the night, but there is no reply, except for the buzzing of invisible machines...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It's crosstalk. In all likelihood..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's crosstalk. In all likelihood they can't hear you. You have to keep trying until we get a signal through."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Keep trying, officer. We'll get a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Keep trying, officer. We'll get a signal through eventually."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einziges Kind. Er kann doch auch nächstes Jahr zur Akademie gehen."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""... It's been a long winter... Lon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... It's been a long winter... Long and cold..."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Something here is eating at the lie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something here is eating at the lieutenant, as much as he would like to move past it.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You actually haven't. But you have..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You actually haven't. But you have proven that you're a relatively capable climber."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Hmm, it seems to have made some di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmm, it seems to have made some difference, but unfortunately not enough to alter the overall situation."

fields.Title: Logic: "The programmer mentioned ammonia, b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The programmer mentioned ammonia, but anything *alcoholic* should dissolve the oils, creating a cleaner (and clearer) connection.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "Across the river, you can see the l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Across the river, you can see the lights of Coalition Warship Archer floating above Revachol East.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "And by that, they mean the ones wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And by that, they mean the ones with the guns and the warships...

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Nein, Liebling! ... unseren Jungen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nein, Liebling! ... unseren Jungen... nach Vredefort ... einem dieser *Dinger*..."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "That performance was, frankly, an e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That performance was, frankly, an embarrassment.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Why not arm the good king's valiant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why not arm the good king's valiant steed instead? There seems to be *just* enough room between its teeth there...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's been a long winter... Long an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's been a long winter... Long and cold."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Officer? Are you in order? We're w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer? Are you in order? We're waiting for you to start..."

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is RCM Officer Tequila Sunset. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Mention what?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mention what?"

fields.Title: You: ""It's cold, like you just said.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's cold, like you just said."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's been a long winter... Long an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's been a long winter... Long and cold."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Truth be told, you have no idea wha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Truth be told, you have no idea what you're looking for. It just looks like a cord attached to a piece of metal. You pick at the colourful rubber jacketing, not sure what else to do...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The signal is clear, the storm has..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The signal is clear, the storm has passed. This is another voice, a live voice, on the other end of this invisible bridge you've established...

fields.Title: Authority: "This is it... you're finally gettin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is it... you're finally getting to speak with those who hold *real* power.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Marianne ... mir erzählt, dass Osk..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Marianne ... mir erzählt, dass Oskar nicht mehr ... seit er auf einem Luftschiff aus Graad zurückgekommen ... halten ihn die Psychologen für vollkommen normal ... aber sie hat das Gefühl ... seit seiner Rückkehr ... einem Fremden zusammenzuleben..."
fields.Alternate1: "Marianne hat mir erzählt, dass Oskar nicht mehr derselbe ist, seit er auf einem Luftschiff aus Graad zurückgekommen ist. Natürlich halten ihn die Psychologen für vollkommen normal, aber sie hat das Gefühl, seit seiner Rückkehr mit einem Fremden zusammenzuleben..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""... someone has been maintaining i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... someone has been maintaining it..." The lieutenant's voice suddenly grows faint and distant, as though he were speaking from a passing motor carriage...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""That's much better. Please, try ag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's much better. Please, try again."

fields.Title: You: "(Sigh.) "Coalition Warship Archer...."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Sigh.) "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Firewalker."
fields.Alternate1: (Sigh.) "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Tequila Sunset."
fields.Alternate2: (Sigh.) "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Detective Costeau."
fields.Alternate3: (Sigh.) "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Lieutenant Du Bois."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The whole monument is covered in a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The whole monument is covered in a thin but durable layer of oil and grime. It's obvious no one has cleaned it in years.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Ideally, narrow the receiving mode..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ideally, narrow the receiving mode, so that we can isolate the warship's signal and eliminate the crosstalk. But if you don't know what you're doing of course you could just make it worse."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Horseback Antenna: "The king won't know what he's missi..."]
Horseback Antenna: "This faithful steed is in nearly as..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This faithful steed is in nearly as poor a condition as its rider.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "Chalk powder. Absorbs moisture and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Chalk powder. Absorbs moisture and keeps your grip firm.

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, what if they *never* acknowl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, what if they *never* acknowledge me?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Go ahead, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Go ahead, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is RCM Officer Firewalker. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Shivers: "A slight frisson at the point where..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A slight frisson at the point where your neck meets your spine. Something about the lieutenant's words, directed at you, but not *you*.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Ah, yes, of course. That must be i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, yes, of course. That must be it..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""... someone has been maintaining i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... someone has been maintaining it..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "You are face to face with Filippe I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You are face to face with Filippe III. The bronze king looks toward the west. Something about his features seems bizarrely distorted.

fields.Title: Endurance: "He seems ill-equipped for wherever..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He seems ill-equipped for wherever he’s going. A king should not go about unarmed.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Everything in order, detective? Yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Everything in order, detective? You're really giving Filippe III a stare."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm sorry! I was trying to do good.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry! I was trying to do good."

fields.Title: You: ""That was pretty bad. I hope nobody..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That was pretty bad. I hope nobody saw it."

fields.Title: You: "Examine the connections."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine the connections.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "To your surprise, the sabre's hilt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To your surprise, the sabre's hilt fits quite snugly in the statue's hand. The king cuts quite the triumphal figure now.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There is no way *that* is going to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There is no way *that* is going to make any difference..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Huh. The signal is coming through..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Huh. The signal is coming through a bit clearer now. Good work."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: "The programmer seems to consider th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The programmer seems to consider the question for a moment, then dismisses it with a flick of her wrist...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks up at you with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks up at you with a nervous glance.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Then he turns to you. He shakes his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Then he turns to you. He shakes his head slightly and looks back at the amplifier.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It isn't gibberish, it's Walder. N..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It isn't gibberish, it's Walder. Now please, keep trying."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""There's no way the lieutenant has..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's no way the lieutenant has his *own* mega-low frequency connection. Very strange..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""I did not expect simply locating t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I did not expect simply locating the signal to be so difficult." She appears to be concentrating very intently.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "No problem at all. You've already t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No problem at all. You've already teleported up *way* greater heights.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You can't help but feel that *sabre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can't help but feel that *sabre* you picked up might just give this old king a little more panache *and* better reception!

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The sky is opaque with dark clouds...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sky is opaque with dark clouds. Somehow, the raindrops seem to fall more slowly from this angle...
fields.Alternate1: The sky is opaque with dark clouds. Snow spirals all around you...

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Down below a little doll-sized lieu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Down below a little doll-sized lieutenant is looking up, shielding his eyes. He's worried for you.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... Nein, Liebling!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Nein, Liebling!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "She's right. This was your responsi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's right. This was your responsibility...

fields.Title: Jump to: [You: ""Okay, let's do this." (Climb the m..."]
Soona, the Programmer: ""There won't *be* any later. This i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There won't *be* any later. This is our chance. Now please, keep going."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einziges Kind..."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, let's do this." (Climb the m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, let's do this." (Climb the monument.)
fields.Sequence: SemiBlack(true,0.3); BanishInterface(true)@2.5; FocusCamera(MonumentClimbCam)@2; TravelTo(Tequila Sunset, MonumentClimbMarker, 2, false)@2; SemiBlack(false,1)@3; PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, monument_climb)@3->Message(inPosition); FocusCamera(MonumentClimbCam2)@4; BanishInterface(false)@Message(inPosition);

fields.Title: Jump to: [Horseback Antenna: "To your surprise, the sabre's hilt..."]
You: "Attempt to narrow the receiving mod..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Attempt to narrow the receiving mode manually.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "Almost immediately, the ammonia beg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Almost immediately, the ammonia begins breaking down the oils around the copper wiring.

fields.Title: You: ""Are you going to tell me you didn'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you going to tell me you didn't say *that*, either?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""...someone has been maintaining it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...someone has been maintaining it. The wiring has been repaired..."

fields.Title: You: ""Are you saying this is more entrop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you saying this is more entroponetic crosstalk, then?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Yes, that's by far the most likely..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, that's by far the most likely explanation. But the odds of us hearing him, though, out of all the voices in the pale..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""...are astronomically low.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "...are astronomically low."

fields.Title: Logic: "But you don't have the technical ex..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But you don't have the technical expertise...

fields.Title: You: ""The connections are pretty dirty,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The connections are pretty dirty, but I don't have anything to clean them with."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... unser einziges Kind. Er kann d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... unser einziges Kind. Er kann doch auch nächstes Jahr zur Akademie gehen..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The sky is gray and overcast. Someh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sky is gray and overcast. Somehow, the raindrops seem to fall more slowly from this angle...
fields.Alternate1: The sky is gray and overcast. Snow spirals all around you...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Try it now, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Try it now, officer."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Aha, excellent! You are connected...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Aha, excellent! You are connected. Now be quick, I don't know how long I'll be able to preserve the signal."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""I'm not joking, officer. I'll only..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not joking, officer. I'll only be able to hold the signal open for a few more moments. What you came here to ask, ask it now..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Time is running short, officer. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Time is running short, officer. I estimate you have time for *maybe* two more questions..."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Soona, the Programmer: ""And now if you'll just connect tha..."]
You: ""Coalition Warship Archer, this is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Firewalker. If you're there, Archer, please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate1: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Tequila Sunset. If you're there, Archer, please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate2: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Detective Costeau. If you're there, Archer, please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate3: "Coalition Warship Archer, this is Lieutenant Du Bois. If you're there, Archer, please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "Your gloves give you a solid grip o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your gloves give you a solid grip on the metal bar. This feels pleasingly familiar...

fields.Title: You: "Keep it to yourself."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep it to yourself.

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer. This is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is RCM Officer Firewalker. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate1: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is RCM Officer Tequila Sunset. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate2: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is Detective Costeau of the RCM. Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate3: "Coalition Warship Archer. This is Lieutenant Du Bois of the RCM. Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""Is everything alright?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is everything alright?"

fields.Title: You: "Where's the sound coming from?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Where's the sound coming from?

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, don't clog my connection.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, don't clog my connection."

fields.Title: You: ""I just heard you say, 'It's cold n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I just heard you say, 'It's cold now'."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I promise you, I didn't, even thou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I promise you, I didn't, even though it certainly *sounds* like me..." The lieutenant seems to wince at the sound of his own voice.

fields.Title: Shivers: "A slight frisson at the point where..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A slight frisson at the point where your neck meets your spine. You can *feel* the lieutenant's presence, even though he's nowhere to be found...

fields.Title: You: "Clean the connections with the ammo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Clean the connections with the ammonia.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "Across the river, you can see Coali..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Across the river, you can see Coalition Warship Archer tracing its gradual circuit above Revachol East.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Nein, Liebling!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nein, Liebling!"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... Walker? Please acknowledge.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Walker? Please acknowledge."
fields.Alternate1: "... Sunset? Please acknowledge."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "It takes a few moments, but the alc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It takes a few moments, but the alcohol gradually begins to break down the oils surrounding the copper wiring.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The cold metal chills your bare han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The cold metal chills your bare hands. Some part of your brain tells you something is missing...

fields.Title: You: "Ignore it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ignore it.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Looking at him now, with both hands..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looking at him now, with both hands on his headphones, you see very briefly what the lieutenant must have been like when he first joined the RCM...

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einziges Kind. Er kann doch auch nächstes Jahr zur Akademie gehen."

fields.Title: You: ""Maybe it's your twin brother?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Maybe it's your twin brother?"

fields.Title: You: ""What is happening?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is happening?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Our transceiver is perfectly capab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Our transceiver is perfectly capable, so there is no problem there..."

fields.Title: You: ""No problem. I've already mastered..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No problem. I've already mastered the art of teleportation."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Hmm, I had hoped that between the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmm, I had hoped that between the signal purifier and cleaning the connections that we would have it, but perhaps I overestimated."

fields.Title: You: "Look down."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look down.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "She yells a single word you can't m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She yells a single word you can't make out, and then shuts the window with a violent *thunk*.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You allow the broken hunk of metal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You allow the broken hunk of metal to clatter to the ground. It wasn't clear to you it did anything anyway...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""That's very good. Just a bit more..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's very good. Just a bit more to the left..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""What else is there to do? Keep try..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What else is there to do? Keep trying."

fields.Title: You: ""How do we change the shape of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How do we change the shape of the antenna?"

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""... Firewalker? Are you there?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Firewalker? Are you there?"
fields.Alternate1: "... Officer Sunset? Are you there?"
fields.Alternate3: "... Lieutenant Du Bois? Are you there?"

fields.Title: Shivers: "Every lightswitch, every motor carr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Every lightswitch, every motor carriage, every doorbell, tea kettle, and radio in Martinaise, all mingled with electrical interference caused by scattered thunderstorms over Ozonne.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It's strangely comforting to think..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's strangely comforting to think of these voices travelling through the air, until you capture them, firefly-like, with your little metal antenna...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""That's true, but I can't leave my..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's true, but I can't leave my station, so it will have to be you."

fields.Title: You: "Pour some alcohol over the connecti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pour some alcohol over the connections.

fields.Title: You: "Look up."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look up.

fields.Title: Empathy: "There is so much you wish you could..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is so much you wish you could ask. Your efforts have bought you some time, but you can't forget what you're *really* here for...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It's making a very *slight* differ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's making a very *slight* difference. The signal is a bit clearer than it was."

fields.Title: Logic: "Hold on, isn't the pale supposed to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hold on, isn't the pale supposed to be thousands of kilometres from here?

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""Come again? We are picking up more..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Come again? We are picking up more interference..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""We're ready to try, at least. Plea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're ready to try, at least. Please, put those on. I've configured the channels so that only your microphone is set to broadcast. We'll both be able to listen, but anyone we reach will only hear *your* voice."

fields.Title: You: ""Soona, is this more of that entrop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Soona, is this more of that entroponetic crosstalk?"

fields.Title: You: ""Soona, I think there are ghosts in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Soona, I think there are ghosts in this radio."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can assure you, it's not my 'twi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can assure you, it's not my 'twin brother'. Though it certainly does *sound* like me..." The lieutenant seems to wince at the sound of his own voice.

fields.Title: You: ""Kim? How did you get on my connect..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim? How did you get on my connection?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Pale? Pale-pale-pale... Seems to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pale? Pale-pale-pale... Seems to be missing from your records.

fields.Title: You: ""But what if I slip and fall...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But what if I slip and fall..."

fields.Title: Logic: "If you had something *alcoholic*, y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If you had something *alcoholic*, you could dissolve the oils, creating a cleaner (and clearer) connection.

fields.Title: You: ""The connections look fine to me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The connections look fine to me."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "A clear night sky. The stars make f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A clear night sky. The stars make for a brilliant display...

fields.Title: You: "Keep it to yourself."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep it to yourself.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Again.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Again."

fields.Title: You: ""Coalition Warship Archer. Do you a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Firewalker."
fields.Alternate1: "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Tequila Sunset."
fields.Alternate2: "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Detective Costeau."
fields.Alternate3: "Coalition Warship Archer. Do you acknowledge? This is Lieutenant Du Bois."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Damn..." The programmer removes he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn..." The programmer removes her sweat-drenched headphones. "Even with the crosstalk suppressed the signal is still very weak."

fields.Title: You: ""Archer! This is Firewalker. Can yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Archer! This is Firewalker. Can you hear me?"
fields.Alternate1: "Archer! This is Tequila Sunset. Can you hear me?"
fields.Alternate2: "Archer! This is Detective Costeau. Can you hear me?"
fields.Alternate3: "Archer! This is Lieutenant Du Bois. Can you hear me?"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... Firewalker? Please respond...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Firewalker? Please respond..."
fields.Alternate1: "... Officer Sunset? Please respond..."

fields.Title: Composure: "Outwardly, they both exude calm, bu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Outwardly, they both exude calm, but there's something disturbing about this thought to both of them.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The rustling of dry autumn leaves...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The rustling of dry autumn leaves. Waves breaking at a distance. A thousand wings beating at once.

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, what are *you* talking about?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, what are *you* talking about?"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The king won't know what he's missi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The king won't know what he's missing. He stares straight ahead, his expression defiant and verdigris.

fields.Title: Empathy: "There is so much you wish you could..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is so much you wish you could ask, but you probably only have time for one or two questions before the signal is lost...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It's not working." The programmer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not working." The programmer removes her sweat-drenched headphones. "The crosstalk is simply too strong."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "The connection itself is nothing mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The connection itself is nothing more than a little braid of exposed wire wrapped about the hoof of the horse, a copper fetter it cannot slip.

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""Firewalker, this is Coalition Wars..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Firewalker, this is Coalition Warship Archer. We are acknowledging and accepting you."
fields.Alternate1: "Officer Sunset, this is Coalition Warship Archer. We are acknowledging and accepting you."
fields.Alternate2: "Detective Costeau, this is Coalition Warship Archer. We are acknowledging and accepting you."
fields.Alternate3: "Lieutenant Du Bois, this is Coalition Warship Archer. We are acknowledging and accepting you."

fields.Title: You: ""Archer! Is that you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Archer! Is that you?"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "A maelstrom of sound, swirling and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A maelstrom of sound, swirling and swirling around an invisible point. It's mounting, mounting...

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""You will need to transmit your con..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You will need to transmit your connection request while I attempt to locate the warship's public frequency. You will likely encounter some interference, but it's important to keep transmitting your request until you're acknowledged. Ready?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""You will need to transmit your con..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You will need to transmit your connection request while I attempt to locate the warship's public frequency. You will likely encounter some interference, but it's important to keep transmitting your request until you're acknowledged. Ready?"

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "He is nervous for your sake, of cou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is nervous for your sake, of course, but also his own.

fields.Title: You: "Keep listening."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep listening.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It's very likely, based on what we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's very likely, based on what we've recently learned. Give me a moment while I attempt to narrow the receiving mode..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Fortunately, we have a more-than-a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fortunately, we have a more-than-adequate transceiver, so I do not believe it is causing any problems..."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Images of your body smashed against..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Images of your body smashed against the pavement flood your mind -- this is *dangerous*.

fields.Title: You: ""Did that help?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did that help?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""What are you doing? The connection..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you doing? The connection is even worse now! This is extremely unprofessional."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""... nicht mehr derselbe ist, seit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... nicht mehr derselbe ist, seit er auf einem Luftschiff aus Graad zurückgekommen ist..."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Nein, Liebling! Das lasse ich nich..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nein, Liebling! Das lasse ich nicht zu … Wie kannst du unseren Jungen bloß auf einem dieser *Dinger* nach Vredefort schicken?"

fields.Title: Interfacing: "The signals are getting increasingl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The signals are getting increasingly mixed. Plucking Archer's signal from this will be like isolating a single strand from a tangle of hair.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Come on, son. This isn't anything b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Come on, son. This isn't anything but a common high bar! Just get a solid overhand grip and hoist yourself up!

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "This faithful steed cuts a dashing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This faithful steed cuts a dashing figure with the replica sabre between its teeth.

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "... and then, nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: ... and then, nothing.

fields.Title: Coalition Warship Archer: ""... Firewalker? Are you there?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "... Firewalker? Are you there?"
fields.Alternate1: "... Officer Sunset? Are you there?"
fields.Alternate3: "... Lieutenant Du Bois? Are you there?"

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einziges Kind. Er kann doch auch nächstes Jahr zur Akademie gehen."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: ""Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Liebling, bitte… Er ist unser einziges Kind. Er kann doch auch nächstes Jahr zur Akademie gehen."

fields.Title: Horseback Antenna: "An uncomfortable silence falls over..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An uncomfortable silence falls over the connection.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""And we're also unlikely to change..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And we're also unlikely to change our local entroponetic conditions. So the next step is to thoroughly inspect our connections."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Short of changing the shape of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Short of changing the shape of the antenna, I'm not sure what else we can do from here. And the lorries are all jammed together, so that's unlikely to happen."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Ah. Very good, officer.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah. Very good, officer."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Are you alright, officer?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you alright, officer?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: "A loud sigh comes through the headp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A loud sigh comes through the headphones. "Be advised, officer. The signal is liable to fail any moment now..."

fields.Title: You: ""Did you *see* that bar work?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did you *see* that bar work?"

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""What do you mean? You adjust the a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you mean? You adjust the antenna, manually, with your hands."

fields.Title: You: "That's brilliant! [Put the sabre be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's brilliant! [Put the sabre between the horse's teeth.]

fields.Title: Composure: "Outwardly, she exudes calm, but the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Outwardly, she exudes calm, but there's something disturbing about this thought to her.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""And now if you'll just connect tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And now if you'll just connect that here..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Good. Beginning transmission.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. Beginning transmission."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""...someone has been maintaining it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "...someone has been maintaining it. The wiring has been repaired..."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Here it is again, this pale... If o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Here it is again, this pale... If only you knew more about it.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Teleportation isn't real. Climbing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Teleportation isn't real. Climbing is, however. With all its hazards."

fields.Title: You: ""But I don't know what I'm doing...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But I don't know what I'm doing..."

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""Then you might break your neck," s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then you might break your neck," she replies matter-of-factly.

fields.Title: Soona, the Programmer: ""It's alright, lieutenant. He's sim..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's alright, lieutenant. He's simply cleaning the connections."

fields.Title: You: "Look at the rider."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the rider.
fields.Alternate1: Look at Filippe III.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Your grip is firm, yet controlled...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your grip is firm, yet controlled. The swelling in your headset guides your hands as much as your hands guide the bronze horse head. It's almost like you're hearing *through* the horse itself...

fields.Dialogue Text: "Please be advised that you are speaking on the public frequency. What is your request?"
